# Rust
/target
**/*.rs.bk
Cargo.lock.bak

# M0 example output
/out.png
/*.png

# premake-fetched dependencies cache (Vulkan-Headers, VMA, vk-bootstrap, ply).
# build.rs points $DEPENDENCIES here; it is large and reproducible, so not committed.
/.rive-deps/

# rive-runtime build artifacts (generated into the submodule's out/ tree by premake+make)
/vendor/rive-runtime/out/
/vendor/rive-runtime/**/out/
/vendor/rive-runtime/dependencies/*_*/

# Vendored premake5 binaries: Linux ELF via tools/fetch_premake.sh (beta2),
# Windows .exe via tools/fetch_premake.cmd (beta7). Not tracked; build.rs falls
# back to $PREMAKE5 / PATH. The fetch scripts themselves ARE tracked.
/tools/premake5
/tools/*.exe
/tools/*.so
/tools/*.so.debug

# Editor / OS
.DS_Store
*.swp

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Local-only — kept on disk for development, NOT published in this repo.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Test .riv assets. Several are third-party (Rive Community / Marketplace
# downloads) or project-specific faces used only for local bring-up while the
# framework matures; their redistribution terms are not cleared for bundling.
# Examples take a `.riv` path (CLI arg / RIVE_RIV env) — see assets/README.md.
/assets/*.riv

# Internal engineering history: milestone reports, design specs, perf logs,
# inception notes, and the cross-project engine brief. Useful locally, but not
# contributor-facing (and some reference private sibling projects). Distilled
# public architecture lives in docs/architecture.md.
/docs/internal/

# Third-party reference docs mirrored locally (Rive's own C++ docs). Not
# redistributed — see https://rive.app/docs for the upstream source.
/docs/cpp/

# Cross-project engine brief (references private sibling repos).
/docs/engine-plugin-rive-spec.md
